<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10548607>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Morphological characteristics of Thelephora pacifica. A. Basidiome in its natural environment; B. Hymenophore displaying distinctive folds and warts; C–D. Macroscopic features of basidiome; E. Tuberculate spores; F. Context hyphae with fibulae; G. Basidia and basidioles; H. Tuberculate spores. Images E–G were captured using a light microscope, while H shows spores observed under a scanning electron microscope (12.9 mm × 7.5 K)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10548607/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

